Example TBX application to show using the OffsetGraphics
class to paint graphics in a Window.

Running the application puts an option on the iconbar that
contains a menu with options to Quit the application and
show information about the application.

Clicking on the iconbar shows the "Graphics" window that
displays a sample of some of the graphics available
via the OffsetGraphics class.

This window has a menu that allows you to save the
window contents as a sprite using the current number
of desktop colours.

The GraphicsWnd.cc source file shows the use of the
OffsetGraphics class.
The SpriteSaveAs.cc/.h files shows how to create a sprite
and save it to file or via RAM Transfer using the SaveAs
tbx object.
